Claims CLAIMS What is claimed is: 1. A system (100) for powering an electrically powered tool downhole in a well (116), the system (100) comprising: production tubing (603) installed in the well (116); a female component (200) connected to the production tubing (603) and comprising: a female component body (202) located in a housing (204); primary coils (214) wound through the female component body (202); and a borehole (206) delineated by an inner circumferential surface of the female component body (202) and having a borehole axis (210), wherein the borehole (206) outlines a shape; a male component (300) electrically connected to the electrically powered tool and configured to be inserted into the borehole (206) of the female component (200), the male component (300) comprising: a male component body (302) having an external surface (306) formed in the shape; secondary coils (314) wound through the male component body (302); and a conduit (308) extending through the male component body (302) and having a conduit axis (312), wherein the borehole axis (210) and the conduit axis (312) line up when the male component (300) is inserted into the borehole (206) of the female component (200); and a split downhole transformer (400) formed by installation of the male component (300) into the female component (200), wherein formation of the split downhole transformer (400) allows power to transfer from a surface (114) location to the electrically powered tool installed in the production tubing (603) downhole in the well (116). 2. The system of claim 1, wherein the male component (300) and the female component (200) are manufactured using steel laminations. 3. The system of claim 1 or 2, wherein the male component (300) comprises a liner (304) extending around a perimeter of the external surface (306) and a core mandrel (310) inserted into the conduit (308). 4. The system of any one of claims 1 to 3, wherein the male component (300) and the female component (200) are manufactured using coated powder metallurgy. 5. The system of claim 4, wherein the coated powder metallurgy uses iron-silicon soft magnetic composites. 6. The system of any one of claims 1 to 5, further comprising centralizing sections (500) installed in series with the male component body (302), formed in the shape, and comprising bearings (502). 7. The system of any one of claims 1 to 6, wherein the shape comprises interconnected lobes (212) formed in a star-like shape. 8. The system of any one of claims 1 to 7, wherein the electrically powered tool downhole further comprises an electric submersible pump system. 9. The system of any one of claims 1 to 8, wherein the male component (300) is located within a pumping tool (614) comprising a pump (124) and a motor (118). 10. The system of claim 9, wherein the pumping tool (614) is configured to be inserted into an interior of the production tubing (603) to allow the male component (300) to mate with the female component (200). 11. A method for powering an electrically powered tool downhole in a well (116), the method comprising: manufacturing (S1200) a female component (200) comprising: a female component body (202) located in a housing (204); primary coils (214) wound through the female component body (202); and a borehole (206) delineated by an inner circumferential surface of the female component body (202) and having a borehole axis (210), wherein the borehole (206) outlines a shape; manufacturing (S1202) a male component (300) comprising: a male component body (302) having an external surface (306) formed in the shape; secondary coils (314) wound through the male component body (302); and a conduit (308) extending through the male component body (302) and having a conduit axis (312); connecting (S1204) the female component (200) to production tubing (603); installing (S1206) the production tubing (603) into the well (116); connecting (S1208) the male component (300) to the electrically powered tool; 

 running (S1210) the male component (300) and the electrically powered tool into an interior of the production tubing (603); inserting (S1212) the male component (300) into the female component (200) downhole in the well (116) to form a downhole split transformer (400) configured to allow power to transfer from a surface (114) location to the electrically powered tool; and powering (S1214) the electrically powered tool using the split downhole transformer (400). 12. The method of claim 11, wherein manufacturing (S1202) the male component (300) and the female component (200) further comprises forming the male component body (302) and the female component body (202) using steel laminations. 13. The method of claim 11 or 12, wherein manufacturing (S1202) the male component (300) further comprises forming a liner (304) around a perimeter of the external surface (306) and inserting a core mandrel (310) into the conduit (308) of the male component (300). 14. The method of any one of claims 11 to 13, wherein manufacturing (S1202) the male component (300) and the female component (200) further comprises forming the male component body (302) and the female component body (202) using coated powder metallurgy. 15. The method of claim 14, wherein forming the male component body (302) and the female component body (202) using coated powder metallurgy further comprises using ironsilicon soft magnetic composites. 16. The method of any one of claims 11 to 15, wherein manufacturing (S1202) the male component (300) further comprises installing centralizing sections (500) formed in the shape and comprising bearings (502) in series with the male component body (302). 17. The method of any one of claims 11 to 16, wherein the shape comprises interconnected lobes (212) formed in a star-like shape. 18. The method of any one of claims 11 to 17, wherein the electrically powered tool downhole further comprises an electric submersible pump system. 19. The method of any one of claims 11 to 18, wherein connecting the male component (300) to the electrically powered tool further comprises connecting the male component (300) to a pumping tool (614) comprising a pump (124) and a motor (118). 20. The method of claim 19, wherein inserting (S1212) the male component (300) into the female component (200) downhole in the well (116) to form the downhole split transformer 

(400) further comprises inserting the pumping tool (614) into the interior of the production tubing (603) to allow the male component (300) to mate with the female component (200).
